IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE LCRDC OFFERS A VARIETY OF PROGRAMS AND SERVICES TO FOSTER ECONOMIC GROWTH AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT. THE LCRDC HELPS LOCAL GOVERNMENTS, ORGANIZATIONS, BUSINESSES, AND INDIVIDUALS ACCESS FEDERAL, STATE, AND OTHER FUNDING SOURCES TO ENHANCE EMPLOYMENT AND BUSINESS OPPORTUNITIES, MAINTAIN AND IMPROVE INFRASTRUCTURE AND PUBLIC SERVICES, REHABILITATE HOUSING, AND DEVELOP PLANS.

IRS990.Desc: COMPREHENSIVE REGIONAL PLANNING AND GRANTS ADMINISTRATION FOR A TEN COUNTY REGION. PROVIDE COMMUNITY AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AND OTHER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. DURING 2017-18, 18 BUSINESSES WERE ASSISTED WITH 28 LOANS, HELPING CREATE 153.5 JOBS; OTHERS ASSISTED WITH TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. 3 NEW INFRASTRUCTURE/PUBLIC FACILITY/HANDICAPPED ACCESSIBILITY PROJECTS ASSISTED AND ADMINISTERED. 1 HOUSING REHABILITATION PROJECT WAS FUNDED. OTHER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO CITIES, COUNTIES, AND COMMUNITY GROUPS WAS PROVIDED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 WILL BE E-MAILED TO THE JOINT FINANCE COMMITTEE FOR REVIEW PRIOR TO FILING. THE 990 IS ALSO E-MAILED TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS FOR REVIEW.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO COMPLETE CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORMS ANNUALLY. IF A CONFLICT OR APPEARANCE OF A CONFLICT ARISES, THE BOARD MEMBER IS REQUIRED TO ABSTAIN FROM VOTING ON ANY ACTION AFFECTED BY THE CONFLICT.
